The ATM brought a motion of no confidence against Ramaphosa in February which was delayed due to the COVID-19 lockdown. The party is suing to force a secret ballot. Courtesy of #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - The ATM is heading to court on Thursday to force a secret ballot in the motion of no confidence in President Cyril Ramaphosa. The party has approached the Western Cape High Court on an urgent basis. READ: ATM calls for Ramaphosa to step down It says National Assembly Speaker Thandi Modise's decision to refuse a secret ballot is irrational and biased. The DA and UDM say they will not participate, describing the motion as frivolous. The ATM brought a motion of no confidence against Ramaphosa in February which was delayed due to the COVID-19 lockdown.